import { VENDORS } from "../data/pf2025/vendors";
import { volunteers } from "../data/pf2025/volunteers";
---

<Layout title="Pond Fest 2025">
  <Image src={PondFest} alt="pond fest logo" id="event-logo" />
  <h2>What is Pond Fest?</h2>
  <h3>Friends of Lums Pond</h3>
  <p>
    Friends of Lums Pond, Inc. is a nonprofit organization dedicated to
    preserving and enhancing Lums Pond State Park through volunteer efforts,
    fundraising, education, and advocacy. Operating independently since 2002, we
    work under a Friends agreement with Delaware State Parks, following their
    standards for volunteer organizations.
  </p>
  <p>
    Come talk to us at the information tables! You could even become a member!

    <br />
     You can read more about <a href={getUrl("resources/membership")}
      >member benefits here</a
    >.
  </p>
  <h3>Pond Fest</h3>
  <p>
    Pond Fest is a concert for a cause hosted by the Friends of Lums Pond State
    Park. Our specific goals for this event are to fund youth scholarships as
    much as possible in 2025 and install an accessible kayak launch ramp.
  </p>
  <p>
    Our group has reached out to our local community including small businesses,
    non-profits, crafters, volunteers, and clubs. The response has been
    incredibly rewarding and positive!
  </p>
  <p>
    Our goal this year is to raise $10,000. Please help us achieve our goal to
    give back to the park and community!
  </p>

  <p>
    We also have event-exclusive merch for sale at the information tables!
    <Image src={PondFestShirt} alt="pond fest shirt" id="event-shirt" />
  </p>
  <p>
    Tag us on social media!
    <br />@FriendsOfLumsPond
    <br />#LumsPond
    <br />#LumsPondFest
    <br />#NatureRocks
    <br />#DEStateParks
  </p>

  <h2>What are we fundraising for?</h2>

  <h3>Youth Scholarships</h3>
  <p>
    Scholarship funds increase access for Title 1 schools (schools with 40% or
    more low-income families) to the outdoors through environmental education
    field trips by reducing the cost barrier to local schools. In the spring of
    2024, Lums Pond had 524 students attend these field trips. Our ultimate goal
    is to subsidize as much of that as possible and enable more students to
    participate. If you'd like to contribute to this program directly, please
    visit our <a href="https://donorbox.org/pond-fest-2025-donations"
      >fundraising campaign here</a
    >.
  </p>

  <h3>Accessible Kayak Launch</h3>
  <p>
    We want to make Lums Pond more accessible so that everyone has the chance to
    enjoy being on the water. This year we are targeting a BoardSafe Accessible
    Kayak Launch, a nationally recognized system designed with adaptive features
    that make it safer and easier for people of all abilities to launch and land
    their kayaks. The launch includes transfer platforms, handrails, and
    stability features that allow users greater independence. By funding this
    project, we will open Lums Pond’s waters to more visitors than ever before.
    If you'd like to contribute to this program directly, please visit our <a
      href="https://donorbox.org/pond-fest-2025-donations"
      >fundraising campaign here</a
    >.
  </p>

  <h3>Our Mission</h3>
  <p>
    We are also raising funds to support our organization's ongoing mission of
    preserving and enhancing Lums Pond State Park in partnership with the DNREC
    park staff.
  </p>

  <h2 id="amenities">Event Amenities & Activities</h2>
  <h4>Event Map</h4>
  <Image src={EventMapImg} alt="event map at pond fest" class="event-map" />

  <h4>Parking Map</h4>
  <p>
    Main parking will be in Area 1 (where the event is located). If needed,
    overflow parking will be available in Area 2, near the playground. Follow
    Pond Fest signs down the short trail to get to Area 1.
  </p>
  <Image src={ParkingMapImg} alt="parking map at pond fest" class="event-map" />
