    <div id="lineup-list-box">
      <h6>Secondhand Stray</h6>
      <h6>FINN</h6>
      <h6>Big Izzy and Bullfrog</h6>
      <h6>The Mad Dabbers</h6>
      <h6>Stealing Society</h6>
      <h6>Adam Molden</h6>
      <h6>Vic Kozar</h6>
      <h6>Acoustic Sinz</h6>
      <h6>Ballet Folklórico</h6>
      <h6>Alyssa Compton</h6>
      <h6>Pet Project</h6>
    </div>
    <div id="lineup-image-box">
      <Image
        src={PondFestLineupImg}
        alt="pond fest lineup"
        id="event-lineup-img"
      />
    </div>
  </div>
  <h4>Live Music Seating</h4>
  <p>
    Relax on the lawn at our Wingspan stage or enjoy picnic seating near the
    Monarch stage.
  </p>

  <h3>Local Brews</h3>
  <p>
    Beer and seltzer will be available for purchase thanks to the generous
    donations of local breweries. Beer tickets can be purchased at Pond Fest HQ.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>JAKL Beer Works</li>
    <li>Volunteer Brewing Company</li>
    <li>First State Brewing Company</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Food Trucks</h3>
   We've got some incredible food trucks lined up this year!
  <ul>
    <li>Dixie's Down Home Cooking</li>
    <li>DE Mex Street Foods</li>
    <li>We Aim To Cheese</li>
    <li>Kona Ice</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Activities</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Hayride through the park (additional purchase)</li>
    <li>Face Painting (additional purchase)</li>
    <li>Delaware R/C Club Display</li>
    <li>Delaware First Responders</li>
    <li>Delaware State Parks “Delawanderer” Airstream</li>
    <li>Large pieces of artwork hand-painted by local families and schools</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>First Responder Displays & Demos</h4>
  <p>
    We're honored to welcome Delaware's first responders to Pond Fest! From 1-3
    PM, you can explore their vehicles, equipment, and displays — and meet the
    heroes who serve our communities every day.
  </p>
  <Image
    src={FirstRespondersMapImg}
    alt="first responders layout"
    class="event-map"
  />

  <h4>Kid Zone!</h4>
  <p>
    We have a ton of fun activities planned for the kids! Kid Zone wristbands
    can be purchased at Pond Fest HQ.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Book Readings</li>
    <li>
      Yard Games:
      <ul>
        <li>Giant jenga blocks</li>
        <li>Horseshoe</li>
        <li>Cornhole</li>
        <li>Connect 4</li>
        <li>Ring toss</li>
        <li>Football throw</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
      Make-and-Take Arts & Crafts:
      <ul>
        <li>pumpkin decorating</li>
        <li>create a bookmark</li>
        <li>popsicle stick dragonflies</li>
        <li>felt decorations (ghosts, leaves, and pumpkins!)</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
      Coloring Stations: paint, crayons, markers, foam stickers, regular
      stickers, etc.
    </li>
    <li>Temporary Tattoo Station</li>
    <li>Kiddie Duck Pond with Prizes</li>
    <li>Nature Scavenger Hunt</li>
    <li>Face Painting (available w/ tickets or wristband)</li>
  </ul>
  <h3>Raffle and Silent Auction</h3>
  <p>
    We'll be raffling and auctioning off a variety of exciting items generously
    donated by Friends of Lums Pond supporters. A few examples include:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>Pond Fest gift basket, including merch and FOLP membership</li>
    <li>Kids "Surf Fishing Vehicle" donated by DNREC</li>
    <li>A week of camping at Lums Pond donated by DNREC</li>
    <li>A pair of passes to Fort Delaware State Park donated by DNREC</li>
    <li>Foursome golf passes donated by Deerfield Golf Club</li>
    <li>Foursome golf passes donated by Garrisons Lake Golf Club</li>
    <li>Various items donated by REI</li>
    <li>A full-size cornhole set, hand-made and donated by Bob Conley</li>
    <li>Hand-made birdhouses donated by Bob Conley</li>
    <li>Band merchandise donated by Lucky Stone</li>
    <li>
      Ceramic painting mini-kit and Gift Card donated by Your Creation Station
    </li>
    <li>Mum and Gift Card donated by Willey Farms</li>
    <li>Artwork donated by local artist and illustrator, Mark Collins</li>
    <li>Restaurant Gift Card donated by Stewart's Brewing Company</li>
    <li>...and more!</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 id="vendors">Vendors, Crafters, and Nonprofits</h3>
  <p>
    We've got over 40 vendors, crafters, and nonprofits lined up for you to
    explore. Check back soon for more details.
  </p>
  <Image
    src={VendorMap}
    alt="vendor map at pond fest"
    id="vendor-map"
    class="pf-maps"
  />
  <table id="by-name">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Name of Business/Organization</th>
        <th>Location</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        {
          VENDORS.map((vendor) => (
            <tr>
              <>
                <td>{vendor.name}</td>
                <td>{vendor.location}</td>
              </>
            </tr>
          ))
        }
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Sponsors</h2>
  <p>
    Friends of Lums Pond would like to extend our deepest gratitude to our
    sponsors for Pond Fest 2025! Together, we are making an impact. We could not
    do it without you!
  </p>

  <h3>Platinum Sponsors</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Granite-Corinthian Lodge No. 34 A.F. & A.M.</li>
    <li>Christiana Care</li>
  </ul>
  <h3>Gold Sponsors</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Superservice Automotive</li>
    <li>MOT Lending Group at Guild Mortgage</li>
    <li>Easterseals Delaware & Maryland's Eastern Shore</li>
  </ul>
  <h3>Silver Sponsors</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Deerfield Golf Club</li>
    <li>Little Bear Dog Care & Training, LLC</li>
    <li>Sit Means Sit</li>
    <li>Academy of Dog Training & Agility</li>
    <li>Bayada Pediatrics</li>
