  <ul>
    <li>Joel Mey & Family</li>
    <li>Jeremy Lambert & Family</li>
    <li>The Rose Family</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Pond Fest Committee</h2>
  <p>
    Behind the music, activities, and community spirit of Pond Fest is a team of
    dedicated volunteers who made it all happen. From booking bands to
    coordinating vendors, designing merch, reaching out to sponsors, gathering
    and making raffle items, hands-on setup, and so much more. This group poured
    their hearts into creating a day for the community to enjoy. We are grateful
    for their energy, vision, and teamwork — Pond Fest would not be possible
    without them!
  </p>
  <b>Our 2025 Committee</b>
  <ul>
    <li>Bob Conley Sr</li>
    <li>Bryan Mey (co-chair)</li>
    <li>Candace Rodriguez</li>
    <li>Chris Grady</li>
    <li>Chriss Funcheon</li>
    <li>Clara Robbs</li>
    <li>Jenny Grady</li>
    <li>Jessie Mey (co-chair)</li>
    <li>John Jacob</li>
    <li>Katie Rose</li>
    <li>Linda Conley</li>
    <li>Mike Cathell</li>
    <li>Morgan Falk</li>
    <li>Patty Jacob</li>
  </ul>
  <b>Want to get involved?</b>
  <p>
    We're already looking ahead to Pond Fest 2026. If you'd like to join the
    planning committee or volunteer your time and talents, stop by the
    information tent or reach out to us at pondfest@friendsoflumspond.org.
  </p>

  <h2>Dear volunteers,</h2>
  <p>
    Thank you for your incredible dedication and hard work in making Pond Fest a
    reality! Your time, energy, and enthusiasm have brought this event to life,
    and we couldn't have done it without you. Whether you were behind the scenes
    or front and center during the event, your contributions have created a
    positive impact on Lums Pond State Park and the community we serve. Your
    commitment not only helps raise essential funds for the park but also
    fosters the spirit of togetherness and volunteerism that makes our park and
    events so special.
  </p>

  <b>Thank you to these amazing humans, our Pond Fest volunteers:</b>
  <ul>
    {volunteers.map((volunteer) => <li>{volunteer}</li>)}
    <li>
      ...and everyone whose contributions made this event possible, including
      those we may not have mentioned.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    With heartfelt appreciation,
    <br />Friends of Lums Pond
  </p>

  <h2>Dear guests,</h2>
  <p>
    Thank you so much for attending our fundraiser. We hope you enjoy your time
    in the park. The amount of interest and feedback for this event from the
    community has been almost overwhelming as if we are all craving something
    positive and pure to pour our hearts into. Lums Pond holds a special place
    in all of our hearts and the friends group is incredibly grateful that you
    support it, too. If it isn't too much trouble, we would greatly appreciate
    your feedback on your experience today by visiting the survey below. This
    will help us make sure to continue the things that went well and improve on
    things that didn't.
  </p>

  <a href="https://forms.gle/fjrmmXqYqzzwueWc6">Feedback Survey</a>

  <p>Thank you for being a friend of Lums Pond.</p>

  <p>
    From all of us,
    <br />Friends of Lums Pond
  </p>

  <i> Pond Fest 2025 - hosted by Friends of Lums Pond State Park</i>
</Layout>

<style>
  .hidden {
    display: none;
  }

  tr:nth-child(even) {
    background-color: #ddd;
  }

  :is(h1, h2, h3, h4, h5, h6) {
    padding-top: 1em;
  }
  ul {
    margin: 0.5em auto 0.5em auto;
  }

  #map-jump {
    display: block;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
    background-color: lightblue;
    border: 1px solid lightskyblue;
    padding: 1rem 2rem;
    margin: 1rem auto;
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

  #event-logo {
    display: block;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    max-width: 60vw;
    width: auto;
    height: auto;
    max-height: 50vh;
  }
  #event-shirt {
    display: block;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    max-width: 60vw;
    width: auto;
    height: auto;
    max-height: 50vh;
  }
  #event-lineup-img {
    display: block;
    max-width: 100%;
    width: auto;
    height: auto;
    margin: auto;
  }
  .event-map {
    max-width: min(90vw, 50rem);
    width: auto;
    height: auto;
    max-height: 80vh;
  }
  .pf-maps {
    max-width: min(90vw, 50rem);
    width: auto;
    height: auto;
    max-height: 80vh;
  }

  #lineup-wrapper {
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  #lineup-list-box {
    max-width: 30%;
    float: left;

    h6 {
      font-size: 1.2em;
      color: var(--color-primary-900);
      line-height: 1.1em;
      padding: 0.4em;
    }
  }
  #lineup-image-box {
    margin: auto;
    width: 69%;
    float: left;
  }
</style>

<script is:inline>
  const sortButton = document.getElementById("sortButton");
  sortButton?.addEventListener("click", function () {
    sortButton.innerText =
      sortButton.innerText === "Sort by name?"
        ? "Sort by location?"
        : "Sort by name?";

    const nameContainer = document.getElementById("by-name");
    nameContainer?.classList.toggle("hidden");

    const locContainer = document.getElementById("by-location");
    locContainer?.classList.toggle("hidden");
  });
</script>
